es to politics and sex. “I have tried to be funny,” Alderman declares, “when occasion has seemed to me to warrant the deployment of a certain humour, which can be a valuable didactic tool and a powerful medium of communication. I have on occasion employed sarcasm and irony. But I have always tried to be scrupulously accurate as to facts, and to locate my comment within that groundwork. Above all, true to my vocation as a rebel who has refused to toe the communal line, I have always presented a point of view that is unashamedly mine.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aJewszGreat BritainxPolitics and governmenty20th century. 0aJewszGreat BritainxPolitics and governmenty21st century. 0aJewszGreat BritainxSocial life and customsy20th century. 0aJewszGreat BritainxSocial life and customsy21st century. 0aJudaismzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 0aJudaismzGreat BritainxHistoryy21st century. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Jewish Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978161811056540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618110565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618110565.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6  Academic Studies Press Backlist eBook-Package 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK